author: COMSOL
description: This example presents a time-dependent study of a microchannel that is used to infuse and flush another piece of equipment with a fluid. The pressure at the five inlets varies sinusoidally as functions of time, and the velocity vector at the outlet is studied. The example uses an extruded prism mesh, which reduces computation time and memory requirements.
